Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.88,0:00:04.45,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Ladies and gentlemen!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.45,0:00:07.67,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I bring you marvelous illusions \Nthat will make the night sparkle!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.67,0:00:11.85,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Tonight's performance features the secret \Nof the Phantom Lady, unknown even to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.53,0:00:18.49,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Hey, Mom, gimme a break already!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.99,0:00:22.20,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,How many hours have you been\N yammering away now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.20,0:00:26.42,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Huh? I haven't even gotten through half \Nthe subjects I want to talk about.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.42,0:00:28.10,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Are you serious?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.10,0:00:29.67,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But, Kaito...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.28,0:00:32.09,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Have you been listening to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.22,0:00:34.67,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,O-Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.67,0:00:36.55,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.55,0:00:38.93,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Because it's something that's very important.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.93,0:00:43.61,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The story of how your \Nfather and I fell in love.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.61,0:00:45.58,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It's just a sappy story...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.56,0:00:47.52,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Did you say something?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.52,0:00:49.20,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,No, nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.20,0:00:51.74,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Then I'll take it from the top once more.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.90,0:00:54.64,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Once was enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.64,0:00:56.99,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It all started 18 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.67,0:01:00.20,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,A Saturday night when the \Nfull moon was bright...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.20,0:01:03.25,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I'll never forget that kiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.25,0:01:05.87,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It was so thrilling and romantic...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.87,0:01:07.37,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.37,0:01:08.96,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That time already?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.96,0:01:11.30,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Mom, I gotta go!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.30,0:01:13.88,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Where are you going at this hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.88,0:01:15.94,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I told you!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.94,0:01:19.13,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,This is one of my \NKid the Phantom Thief nights!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.13,0:01:25.02,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Oh, Darling...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.39,0:01:26.93,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Long time no see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.95,0:03:01.96,Signs - Thief Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(1000,0)}Enter: The Phantom Lady
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.43,0:03:03.38,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.55,0:03:06.34,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Kid the Phantom Thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.45,0:03:10.94,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,This is Nakamori!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.94,0:03:15.26,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Kid the Phantom Thief has stolen the \Njewel and escaped into the crowd!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.64,0:03:18.41,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But, Inspector, Kid is using a hang glider...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.41,0:03:20.58,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That's his usual decoy!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.58,0:03:23.98,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Don't let anybody out of the museum \Nuntil they've had a full body check!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.57,0:03:26.94,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Why can't I leave?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.94,0:03:29.94,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,If you don't hurry, Kid's gonna get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.69,0:03:32.40,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,W-Wait a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.81,0:03:35.09,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I'm Aoko Nakamori!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.09,0:03:38.87,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I just came to drop off my \Ndad's brown bag! Can't I go home?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.36,0:03:41.36,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,, B-Brown bag?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.36,0:03:43.54,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That's Inspector Nakamori's daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.54,0:03:44.82,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Didn't you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.82,0:03:46.84,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,P-Pardon me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.84,0:03:49.73,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That's okay. Keep up the good work!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.38,0:03:53.30,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Good luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.13,0:04:02.14,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Aoko! I borrowed your face again!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.14,0:04:07.65,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Well, looks like it's not the \Njewel I'm {\i1}really{\i0} after...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.07,0:04:11.30,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Guess I'll send this one back \Nto Inspector Nakamori, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.91,0:04:14.11,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Still, this is curious...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.11,0:04:18.77,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,A sticker with a message was \Non the bottom of the jewel...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.44,0:04:24.62,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Kid the Phantom Thief, it's my turn next.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.62,0:04:27.57,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Saturday night, under the full moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.57,0:04:31.41,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I shall seize the jewel upon the \Nhead of the untarnished nail
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.41,0:04:34.86,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and thus repay the debt I owe you \Nfrom 18 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.33,0:04:37.97,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What the hell does it mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.97,0:04:41.12,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,"The head of the untarnished nail"...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.12,0:04:44.69,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I wasn't even born 18 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.31,0:04:48.78,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't know, but they \Nprobably have the wrong guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.72,0:04:53.57,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,All right. This'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.72,0:04:53.57,Signs,,0,0,0,,Nakamori Ginzo-dono\NMetro Police Dept., Second Investigation Division
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.18,0:05:07.17,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,He makes his way through tight security \Nas if performing a magic trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.17,0:05:10.67,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The Magician Under the Moonlight... \NKid the Phantom Thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.16,0:05:12.63,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,How does he do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.24,0:05:19.09,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,There is a person who can walk right through \Nthat tight net without being checked.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.12,0:05:21.60,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I'm talking about...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.20,0:05:24.31,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,...Aoko Nakamori.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.91,0:05:31.52,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The world's greatest thief and this girl seem \Nto have a close relationship, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.52,0:05:33.72,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But, President Gouzu,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.72,0:05:38.68,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,she's the daughter of Inspector Nakamori \Nfrom the Second Investigation Division.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.68,0:05:42.25,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Kid probably just disguised himself \Nas her because it was convenient...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.25,0:05:44.75,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,This would make the fifth such occasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.75,0:05:49.52,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Th-Then Kid and the daughter of the inspector \Nin charge of catching him are...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.52,0:05:50.78,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.78,0:05:53.21,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Yes, that {\i1}is{\i0} the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.58,0:06:00.39,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Magicians use the psychology of disbelief \Nto pull pigeons out of impossible places,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.39,0:06:02.60,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,much to our bafflement.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.64,0:06:05.97,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Don't you think it's strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.97,0:06:12.15,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Why do you suppose Kid returns most of the \Njewels he steals to Inspector Nakamori?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.15,0:06:17.77,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,True. He could just as well return them to \Nother detectives or who he stole them from.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.77,0:06:21.74,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But some of those people might not be honest \Nabout getting the jewels back from Kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.74,0:06:26.08,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,In other words, Kid trusts \NInspector Nakamori.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.08,0:06:27.62,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It's not trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.28,0:06:34.59,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Ginzo Nakamori controls Kid the \NPhantom Thief from behind the scenes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.44,0:06:40.55,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,He made his daughter inherit the role \Nof Kid, prepares her escape routes,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.55,0:06:44.06,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and has her return\N the stolen gems to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.06,0:06:48.27,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,This also explains why he \Nfails to catch Kid every time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.27,0:06:53.50,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,B-But that girl's been seen many times \Nwhile Kid's been pulling a robbery!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.50,0:06:55.06,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That's a stand-in.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.06,0:07:02.24,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Given her skills, it would be a simple feat \Nto employ another girl to dress up as her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.24,0:07:05.04,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But then what are they after?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.04,0:07:11.31,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,All I know is that I've suffered \Nfor 18 long years thanks to Kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.60,0:07:15.86,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But there's no need to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.86,0:07:17.80,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The bait has been put out,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.80,0:07:22.43,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and soon I'll reveal that Kid is working \Nfor her father, Inspector Nakamori,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.43,0:07:26.62,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and that under that cape and tux is \Nan average high school student!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.80,0:07:30.43,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Kaito!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.88,0:07:33.00,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.00,0:07:34.66,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What do I think of what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.66,0:07:36.69,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,As always, your chest hasn't developed...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.69,0:07:39.40,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The hairpin, you dope, the hairpin!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.40,0:07:40.74,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It's cute, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.74,0:07:43.11,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Yeah, sure. Really cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.65,0:07:46.24,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Don't make any unnecessary changes, dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.24,0:07:48.67,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You're making it harder for me \Nto disguise myself as you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.92,0:07:53.29,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That's hairpin's got an interesting shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.46,0:07:56.59,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It's shaped like Toto Tower!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.59,0:07:58.59,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It came with the invitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.59,0:07:59.98,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Invitation?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.98,0:08:07.70,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I won two tickets to a reserved dinner in \Nthe special observation platform of Toto Tower!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.70,0:08:11.10,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Special observation platform... \NIsn't that at the very top?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.62,0:08:17.25,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Yeah! Having a delicious meal with a \Nbeautiful night view... I can't wait for Saturday!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.25,0:08:19.85,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But that special observation platform...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.85,0:08:24.57,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Aren't they using it to exhibit some \Ndead rich guy's private collection?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.09,0:08:29.33,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I saw on the news that,\N just before he died,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.33,0:08:33.54,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,he bought a big-ass ruby that they're gonna \Nput on display from next week, I think...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.54,0:08:35.04,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.04,0:08:40.63,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I'm sure Kid is targeting that ruby, so \NI invited my dad so he can check it out,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.63,0:08:47.26,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,but he said, "I'll be there on a stakeout \Nnext week anyway, so go with a friend!"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.26,0:08:49.04,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Say no more.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.04,0:08:51.21,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I guess I can make it...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.21,0:08:52.62,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.62,0:08:54.18,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I beat you to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.71,0:08:56.74,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,A-Akako?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.74,0:09:00.81,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That red tower was depressed after \NBell Tree Tower surpassed its height,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.81,0:09:06.53,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,so given the "red" in my name, Akako, \NI'd feel bad if I didn't show up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.00,0:09:10.02,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What, you wanted to go, Kaito?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.02,0:09:11.45,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,N-Not especially!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.45,0:09:14.52,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Too bad you don't get to case the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.00,0:09:18.93,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,There's something fishy about the invitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.93,0:09:22.52,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Nakamori-san said she doesn't \Nremember entering any contest.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.52,0:09:29.39,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Maybe someone who knows about your other \Nidentity has set a trap, using her to lure you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.39,0:09:32.98,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Well, try not to stand out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.98,0:09:35.64,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Like they say, the nail that \Nsticks out gets hammered.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.64,0:09:37.64,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Nail that sticks out...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.19,0:09:39.86,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,D-Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.86,0:09:44.36,Signs,,0,0,0,,Blue Parrot
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.46,0:09:44.06,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That does indeed sound suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.87,0:09:49.78,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Maybe Akako was right, that \Nsomebody's laying a trap for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.78,0:09:52.60,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,"Saturday night, under the full moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.60,0:09:57.00,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I shall seize the jewel upon \Nthe head of the untarnished nail,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.00,0:10:00.62,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and thus repay the debt I owe you \Nfrom 18 years ago."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.21,0:10:03.75,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,18 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.75,0:10:05.96,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Jii-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.96,0:10:10.34,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,18 years ago. That sticks in my mind...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.34,0:10:15.23,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it... \NWhere did I hear that recently?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.23,0:10:18.06,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That aside, did you get that \Nstuff together like I asked?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.73,0:10:20.06,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I prepared it...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.52,0:10:22.44,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,...right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.44,0:10:26.81,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Then the outfit I need is all set!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.81,0:10:30.65,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Yes. This time, the preparations were cheap.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.65,0:10:34.02,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It seems that's his one good suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.65,0:10:36.20,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I figured.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.20,0:10:39.58,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I never see him wear anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.58,0:10:43.54,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But I was surprised!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.54,0:10:46.83,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,When you suddenly said \Nyou could make it, Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.83,0:10:51.01,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Given the occasion, Superintendent \NChaki insisted that I come.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.43,0:10:55.47,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Akako-kun. I'm sure you \Nwere looking forward to it...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.47,0:10:56.47,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.77,0:11:01.36,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I was looking out for you, jerk!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.36,0:11:03.23,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You're killing my foot!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.23,0:11:04.78,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Have fun,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.78,0:11:07.64,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,inspector with the crooked mustache.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.74,0:11:09.70,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Mustache?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.05,0:11:11.94,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Don't get pissed at me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.94,0:11:18.16,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I don't know why, but the invitation \NAoko got may be a lure to get me here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.04,0:11:23.63,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.63,0:11:26.16,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,So many things in the collection!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.16,0:11:28.34,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It's like a museum in the sky!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.40,0:11:35.18,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Sheesh, all of that fine art pales in \Ncomparison to this beautiful night view.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.73,0:11:40.01,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,They say the owner of this \Ncollection loved Toto Tower
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.01,0:11:42.64,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and wanted to have an exhibition here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.12,0:11:45.82,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,And yet, nobody else is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.82,0:11:49.65,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,If we're having dinner here, you'd \Nthink there'd be a waitress at least...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.65,0:11:52.04,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It looks like you can get in this car!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.64,0:11:57.30,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It says if you turn the key,\N the engine will roar!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.30,0:12:00.79,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,More like, the prerecorded \Nsound of an engine will play...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.74,0:12:04.59,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,This is awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.59,0:12:06.17,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Exhaust is coming out!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.17,0:12:08.17,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Can this car move?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.24,0:12:12.76,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,A-Aoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.72,0:12:17.84,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Handcuffs and knockout gas!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.84,0:12:19.48,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Then this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.48,0:12:21.60,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Long time no see,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.60,0:12:23.46,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Kid the Phantom Thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.07,0:12:27.61,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,18 years, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.61,0:12:30.07,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Who the hell is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.07,0:12:36.00,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Though you hung up your cape \Nand became a police inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.00,0:12:41.79,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Still, you had your snoozing daughter \Nover there inherit the role.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.79,0:12:43.79,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Hey, wait one second.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.79,0:12:46.45,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,This guy's barking up the wrong tree!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.45,0:12:49.40,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But this situation feels familiar...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.40,0:12:50.50,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Deja vu?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.12,0:12:57.72,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What's this? Don't tell me you came here \Nnot realizing it was my trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.27,0:13:01.89,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The message on the jewel \Npointed to this place,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.89,0:13:05.04,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,while the invitation was an obvious trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.04,0:13:10.19,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It was all a contrivance so I could see what \Nyou would do before this, the final act.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.74,0:13:14.65,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But it looks like I overestimated you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.65,0:13:19.12,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,On a whim, I enclosed that hairpin \Nwith a bugging device inside of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.12,0:13:23.58,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,but instead of destroying it, \Nyour daughter just put it in her hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.96,0:13:27.29,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I knew it was a trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.73,0:13:34.76,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The "head of the untarnished nail" refers to \Nthe head of a nail before a hammer hits it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.19,0:13:40.84,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,In other words, the top of Toto Tower, \Nwhich escaped getting hammered
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.84,0:13:43.72,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,by the taller Bell Tree Tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.89,0:13:48.05,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,So you did catch the "nail that \Nsticks out gets hammered" reference.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.05,0:13:51.69,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But what are you going to do? The \Nsituation is just like in the old days,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.69,0:13:56.41,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,but unlike then, your partner \Nhere isn't worth a damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.41,0:13:58.15,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Partner?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.15,0:14:04.49,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,"The Female with 20 Faces" who dropped \Nout of sight in Paris 18 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.49,0:14:06.54,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The gentlewoman thief...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.88,0:14:10.50,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,...the Phantom Lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.50,0:14:13.13,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Phantom Lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.64,0:14:16.33,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I see! It's not deja vu!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.33,0:14:21.97,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,He's the guy from 18 years ago... \NMom told me this story the other day!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.99,0:14:27.56,Signs,,0,110,11,,{\a7}{\fad(500,0)}18 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.02,0:14:33.98,Main Dialog,,0,0,11,,Hey! Hello? Hello? Hello?! What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.81,0:15:03.55,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,One...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.17,0:15:05.06,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Two...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.66,0:15:06.72,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Three!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.06,0:15:29.29,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,As I figured...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.84,0:15:31.29,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It's a fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.48,0:15:34.25,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Bravo!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.40,0:15:39.62,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That was a brilliant performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.62,0:15:46.22,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Although using fake gore to scare a cop \Nto the point of fainting isn't my style.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.22,0:15:49.46,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I would have gone with \Na more elegant method
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.46,0:15:52.81,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,to send them off to dreamland.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.81,0:15:54.52,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,W-Who are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.09,0:15:57.31,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Toichi Kuroba.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.31,0:15:59.73,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I'm a simple magician.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.90,0:16:06.37,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Toichi Kuroba. I know of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.29,0:16:11.06,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You traveled the world performing \Nmagic shows as a teenager,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.06,0:16:17.34,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and won first prize at the FISM tournament, \Nthe Magician Olympics, at the age of 20.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.34,0:16:19.64,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You were a prodigy when it came to magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.75,0:16:25.30,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But what's a celebrity like you \Ndoing in a place like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.30,0:16:27.47,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,And wearing such a flashy outfit?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.47,0:16:32.68,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I had this suit custom-made for \Nmy magic show in Paris next month.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.37,0:16:38.36,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It's an homage to Arsene Lupin, \NFrance's great gentleman thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.36,0:16:43.76,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,H-He's casually walking over \Nwithout any night-vision goggles!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.76,0:16:47.03,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me he remembers the \Npositions of all the lasers?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.03,0:16:49.22,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You're after...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.22,0:16:53.50,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,...the motorcycle of the recently-departed \Nfamous French motorcycle racer,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.50,0:16:57.96,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,embedded with a diamond to \Ncommemorate his victories.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.96,0:17:03.42,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The showpiece of the bike exhibition here\N on the top floor of {\i1}La Grande Dame de Fer.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.98,0:17:07.34,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, that's a fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.95,0:17:13.39,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Word gets out it's been stolen, and soon you \Ncan buy "the real one" on the black market.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.39,0:17:20.70,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Phantom Lady reappears after a two-year \Nabsence, but stealing this isn't worth your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.70,0:17:27.03,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What else can I do?! Somebody sent out a \Nnotice saying I was going to steal it tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.66,0:17:29.58,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You can give me the details later.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.58,0:17:31.79,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Let me drop you off downstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.28,0:17:35.04,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Idiot. I'm riding this out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.04,0:17:38.96,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Replica or not, I'm delivering \Nit to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.96,0:17:40.73,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't do that if I were you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.12,0:17:44.78,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,See? What'd I tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.78,0:17:46.78,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,W-What's with the handcuffs?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.78,0:17:50.05,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It means I have no more use for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.49,0:17:54.56,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You should've stayed home, \Ngloating over all the stolen jewels.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.94,0:17:59.78,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But instead, you kept returning \Nthe loot to the police,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.78,0:18:05.36,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,putting a major dent in my business as I got \Nall these replicas in stock but no buyers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.19,0:18:06.82,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.49,0:18:09.69,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I didn't know you worked with assistants.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.69,0:18:11.28,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,He's no assistant of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.28,0:18:16.05,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Anyway, if the Phantom Lady is \Ncaptured stealing the treasure,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.05,0:18:18.46,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,doesn't that put a crimp \Nin your plans?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.18,0:18:20.72,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,No worries there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.72,0:18:26.29,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I've already got a trained Phantom Lady \Nimpersonator on standby.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.29,0:18:29.43,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,And no sense having two of you, \Nso you'll disappear for good...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.10,0:18:36.64,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.64,0:18:37.31,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Cool it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.87,0:18:40.16,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,This is the only exit.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.16,0:18:44.18,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,As long as we block the elevator, \Nthey've got no way out...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.18,0:18:46.18,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I don't know about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.87,0:18:56.44,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.96,0:18:59.73,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Hey! What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.73,0:19:01.22,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.22,0:19:03.17,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I'm dropping you off at the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.17,0:19:05.05,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,D-Dropping me off?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.05,0:19:06.63,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,We're just falling!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.96,0:19:10.34,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,First, I'll silence that...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.95,0:19:12.34,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,...annoying sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.07,0:19:23.94,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,As I suspected, there was a jewel...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.94,0:19:26.98,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,...behind that mask.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.98,0:19:29.53,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Why are you talking like an idiot?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.53,0:19:32.48,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You, me, and the motorcycle \Nare going to hit the ground!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.48,0:19:35.45,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Who do you think I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.16,0:19:38.73,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I don't believe it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.22,0:19:49.92,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Toichi-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.92,0:19:54.57,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,As you requested, I staged an \Naccident to seal off the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.57,0:19:58.12,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,But many bystanders have cameras,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.12,0:20:01.35,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,so I don't think you can use \Nthat costume for the show.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.87,0:20:03.20,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.20,0:20:07.54,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I'll use this costume \Nas a phantom thief instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.32,0:20:14.12,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,A thief so great that the world will \Nforget all about the Phantom Lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.31,0:20:19.15,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,So I'd like you to retire \Nfrom being a phantom thief
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.15,0:20:23.50,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,and stay nice and safe \Nin my jewelry box.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.63,0:20:29.38,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That doesn't sound bad, \Nbut that jewelry box...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.42,0:20:33.80,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,There aren't any other \Njewels in it, are there?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.80,0:20:35.30,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.30,0:20:39.89,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I see! This situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.52,0:20:45.35,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It's just like what Mom was gushing \Nabout, how she and Dad first met!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.35,0:20:48.53,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Then this old fart is the guy
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.53,0:20:52.32,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,whose crooked business was ruined \Nby Mom and Dad 18 years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.32,0:20:55.59,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,So, what are you going to do,\N Kid the Phantom Thief?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.59,0:20:59.76,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,You can try to escape in \Nthat car like 18 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.76,0:21:01.74,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,except it was a\N slim motorcycle then.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.26,0:21:08.17,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,That car is compact, but not enough to fit \Nthrough the windows of this observation deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.64,0:21:13.34,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Although, being a replica, \Nyou can't drive it in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.85,0:21:19.35,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I see. Then this entire \Nprized collection is a hoax.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.35,0:21:23.86,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,And as for the big-ass ruby coming \Nin next week, it's actually a fake
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.86,0:21:28.10,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,that you'll say was stolen by Kid, \Nand then sell replicas on the black market.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.10,0:21:32.57,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,It's all been arranged.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.53,0:21:44.83,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Well, things look a little \Ndicey for me there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.83,0:21:48.26,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,The illusion must go on!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.42,0:23:23.08,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Just when I recall Mom's nostalgic tale,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.08,0:23:24.94,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I find myself in a big pinch in the present!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.94,0:23:30.10,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Still, if I can't slip out of this one, \NI don't have the right to succeed Dad as Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.10,0:23:33.48,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,I've gotta clean up the mess from \NMom's reckless behavior, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.48,0:23:36.11,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Uh-oh! {\i1}He{\i0} showed up?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.11,0:23:38.48,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Then things definitely \Nwon't go according to plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.48,0:23:43.07,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Next time on {\i1}Magic Kaito 1412{\i0}:\N Phantom Lady and the Ryoma Treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.48,0:23:43.07,Signs,,0,0,0,,Phantom Lady and the Ryoma Treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.07,0:23:46.20,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Step right this way! Watch carefully!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.20,0:23:48.75,Main Dialog,,0,0,0,,Don't miss the illusion!
